## Quick Start

### Prerequisites

- Go 1.22+
- Bun 1.1+
- Docker (optional, for containerized builds)
- kubectl + Kind (optional, for local K8s development)

### Development

Clone the repository:

```bash
git clone {{.Module}}.git
cd {{.Name}}
```

Install dependencies and start development servers:

```bash
# Backend API (http://localhost:8080)
make dev-api

# Frontend (http://localhost:5174)
make dev-web
```

Run quality gates:

```bash
make lint       # Linters
make typecheck  # TypeScript
make test       # Unit + integration tests
```

Run E2E tests:

```bash
make e2e-web              # Playwright tests
make e2e-web-integration  # Web + API integration
```

### Production Deployment

Build and deploy to AKS using Helm:

```bash
make build
docker build -t {{.Name}}:latest .
docker push {{.Name}}:latest

helm upgrade --install {{.Name}} ./deploy/helm/{{.Name}} \
  --namespace default \
  --create-namespace
```

